ollars*. Also in practice banks do things like this =E2=80=94=C2=A0credit-c=
ard points programs mostly =E2=80=94=C2=A0and they are in some sense exchan=
geable for dollars, create dollar obligations for the banks, etc., but I ha=
ve not actually made any such claims about my hypothetical loyalty points. =
They could just be numbers on a list.[4] In a footnote to yesterday=E2=80=
=99s column I basically took Bitfinex=E2=80=99s word for this =E2=80=94 =E2=
=80=9CAt the time of the hack Bitfinex did various things to make it up to =
the holders whose money was lost, so I am not sure to what extent Bitfinex'=
s 2016 account-holders still have open claims on these Bitcoins,=E2=80=9D  =
I wrote =E2=80=94=C2=A0but that was kind of dumb and I do not generally  ta=
ke Bitfinex=E2=80=99s word for things.=C2=A0[5] It does *not* exactly say t=
hat the trade has to settle within two business days. It says that the trad=
e=C2=A0=E2=80=94=C2=A0the =E2=80=9Ccontract for the purchase or sale of a s=
ecurity=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94=C2=A0has to=C2=A0=E2=80=9Cprovide for payment of=
 funds and delivery of securities later than the second business day=C2=A0a=
fter the date of the contract unless otherwise expressly agreed to by the p=
arties at the time of the transaction.=E2=80=9D The trade has to *provide f=
or* T+2 settlement =E2=80=94=C2=A0each side has to be *contractually obliga=
ted* to settle in two days =E2=80=94=C2=A0but if they don=E2=80=99t, if the=
y =E2=80=9Cfail,=E2=80=9D that is covered by different provisions. And in f=
act trades do sometimes fail to settle in two days, which is at least annoy=
ing and also provides fodder for a lot of short-selling conspiracy theories=
.[6] I=E2=80=99m citing the field =E2=80=9C% Out=E2=80=9D at the top of the=
 HDS page, BK <equity> HDS <go>.[7] GameStop is higher mostly because 12% o=
f its stock is owned by Ryan Cohen=E2=80=99s investment vehicle. Incidental=
ly, these numbers do not account for short sellers. If 20% of a company=E2=
=80=99s stock is sold short, then long holders will own 120% of its shares.=
 Occasionally you will get a company with (1) mainly institutional ownershi=
p and (2) a lot of shorts, and the total number of disclosed holdings will =
exceed 100%. Don=E2=80=99t tell any of the GameStop holders about that thou=
gh.
